{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"04485cc4-7e28-4831-8b79-1b4261a05fac","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — MSTest.Sdk gives you the simplest possible config:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` automatically pulls in `MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`. No explicit `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution** — add a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>          <!-- 0 = use all available cores -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>    <!-- or ClassLevel -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr, equivalently, add the assembly-level attribute in a file like `TestSetup.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.Method)]\n```\n\n**3. Make database tests run sequentially** — use `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]                   // Runs alone, never overlapping other tests\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void CanInsertRecord() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void CanQueryRecords() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n### How it works\n\n| Attribute | Effect |\n|---|---|\n| `[Parallelize]` (assembly) | All test methods run in parallel by default |\n| `[DoNotParallelize]` (class) | That class's tests wait until no other tests are running |\n| `[DoNotParallelize]` (method) | Just that one method is isolated |\n\nTests marked `[DoNotParallelize]` are executed **after** all parallelizable tests finish, ensuring no concurrent access to your database.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"66b3e586-f47f-4239-8a4b-935c82088b29","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there are no plugins to reference. Let me provide the answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk, parallel execution, and sequential test control.","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"E3C0:2CBD0C:1985E0A:1C800C5:6A052B73"},"id":"2b92b160-0130-49fc-8d7c-2ac6e8460c9e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:55:13.963Z","parentId":"aee844b3-b615-4176-83ff-b654af2d11cf"}
